{"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/openswiftui\/hstack\/geometrygroup()"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"nonisolated"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"geometryGroup"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"some"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP","text":"View"},{"kind":"text","text":"\n"}],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","text":"Discussion","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"By default OpenSwiftUI views push position and size changes down"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"through the view hierarchy, so that only views that draw"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"something (known as leaf views) apply the current animation to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"their frame rectangle. However in some cases this coalescing"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"behavior can give undesirable results; inserting a geometry"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"group can correct that. A group acts as a barrier between the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"parent view and its subviews, forcing the position and size"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"values to be resolved and animated by the parent, before being"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"passed down to each subview."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The example below shows one use of this function: ensuring that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the member views of each row in the stack apply (and animate"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"as) a single geometric transform from their ancestor view,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"rather than letting the effects of the ancestor views be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"applied separately to each leaf view. If the members of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"ItemView","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" may be added and removed at different times the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"group ensures that they stay locked together as animations are"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"applied."}]},{"code":["VStack {","    ForEach(items) { item in","        ItemView(item: item)","            .geometryGroup()","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Returns: a new view whose geometry is isolated from that of its"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"parent view."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"metadata":{"title":"geometryGroup()","externalID":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewPAAE13geometryGroupQryF::SYNTHESIZED::s:15OpenSwiftUICore6HStackV","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"geometryGroup"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"some"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"View"}],"modules":[{"name":"OpenSwiftUI","relatedModules":["OpenSwiftUICore"]}],"platforms":[{"deprecated":false,"introducedAt":"13.0","name":"iOS","unavailable":false,"beta":false},{"deprecated":false,"introducedAt":"10.15","name":"macOS","unavailable":false,"beta":false},{"deprecated":false,"introducedAt":"13.0","name":"tvOS","unavailable":false,"beta":false},{"deprecated":false,"introducedAt":"1.0","name":"visionOS","unavailable":false,"beta":false},{"deprecated":false,"introducedAt":"6.0","name":"watchOS","unavailable":false,"beta":false}],"role":"symbol","symbolKind":"method","remoteSource":{"url":"https:\/\/github.com\/OpenSwiftUIProject\/OpenSwiftUI\/blob\/main\/Sources\/OpenSwiftUICore\/Render\/RendererEffect\/RendererEffect.swift#L304","fileName":"RendererEffect.swift"},"roleHeading":"Instance Method","extendedModule":"OpenSwiftUICore"},"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/HStack\/geometryGroup()","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI","doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/HStack"]]},"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Isolates the geometry (e.g. position and size) of the view"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"from its parent view."}],"references":{"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI/HStack/geometryGroup()":{"role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"geometryGroup","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"some","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"View","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"title":"geometryGroup()","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Isolates the geometry (e.g. position and size) of the view"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"from its parent view."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/HStack\/geometryGroup()","url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui\/hstack\/geometrygroup()"},"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI/View":{"url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui\/view","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"View","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","title":"View","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A type that represents part of your app’s user interface and provides"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"modifiers that you use to configure views."}],"fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"View","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View"},"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI":{"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Declare the user interface and behavior for your app on every platform."}],"url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui","type":"topic","title":"OpenSwiftUI","role":"collection"},"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI/HStack":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/HStack","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"A view that arranges its subviews in a horizontal line.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"HStack"}],"title":"HStack","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"HStack","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui\/hstack"}}}